@node MAINSCREEN "Arkanos V3.0 - Title Screen"

  When you double click on the programm, you see a big "LOADING..."
  screen and some information below. Ignore that for the moment. You
  can configure the game to your needs from the startup. But first you
  need to know what you configure. The first time please read the
  sections as they appear in the main menu of the document.

  Next a little animation comes up. After that the main menu appears.
  On the right you see the menu buttons, and on the left you have the
  quick information pages. Click the PREVIOUS or FORWARD buttons to
  switch through the four pages. Move the mouse over an item and wait
  there to get a short help text. Now the menu buttons on the right,
  from top to bottom:

  @{IT "Paddle type:"}
  @{IT "~~~~~~~~~~~~"}
    Here you can choose between the traditional konvex paddle and real
    physics. With the convex paddle the ball reflects like from a half
    circle around your paddle. It's the easy method that most people
    are familiar with. With the real physics you must move the paddle to
    change the ball's direction. @{"Click here" link RealPaddle.IFF/MAIN} to see the basic concept.
    At position @{B}N@{UB} the paddle does not move. At position @{B}1@{UB} the paddle
    moves along the ball direction and the ball direction levels off.
    At position @{B}2@{UB} the paddle moves against the ball direction and the
    ball direction rises. The more you move the paddle at ball impact,
    the greater will be this effect.

  @{IT "Bonus type:"}
  @{IT "~~~~~~~~~~~"}
    This button changes how bonus items fall down. With the normal mode
    the bonus items fall straight down with constant speed. With the
    enhanced mode the ball "cuts out" the bonus from removed blocks.
    The initial moving direction of the bonus item depends on the ball
    and changes downwards with gravity force!

  @{IT "Mixing mode:"}
  @{IT "~~~~~~~~~~~~"}
    This button simply changes between normal linear level playing and
    mixing all levels in groups of 50 levels. When mixing the levels
    you get 50% more jackpot score, block hits count 2 points more and
    the final bonus is 50000 points instead of 20000 points.

  @{IT "Start New Game"}
  @{IT "~~~~~~~~~~~~~~"}
    Click here to start a new game with the current level set and the
    settings of the previous three buttons. These settings can not
    be changed anymore!

  @{IT "Load Game"}
  @{IT "~~~~~~~~~"}
    Before version 2.0 I used passwords, but with the game statistic
    it would be too complex for a password system.
    Here the "Saves" folder is searched for valid save games and you
    can select one to load. If the save game uses a different level-set
    it will be loaded too. Finally you can see the game settings with
    some other information.

  @{IT "Load Levels"}
  @{IT "~~~~~~~~~~~"}
    Here also the file selector appears and you can load a different
    level-set to play. You can create level-sets with @{"my editor" link EDITOR}.
    Select a file to load the new levels with the high score.

  @{IT "Show Hiscore"}
  @{IT "~~~~~~~~~~~~"}
    Here you can look at the top 10 players for the loaded level-set.
    Each line has the name, the score and a button where you can see
    the @{"statistic" link STATSCREEN} of the game.

  @{IT "Game Options"}
  @{IT "~~~~~~~~~~~~"}
    The options screen has been added with version 2.0. There are no
    changes here, except the display. You can still clear the high
    score merge with another high score and export the high score as
    text file, but without the statistic. And there is information
    about the loaded music modules and free memory.
    And you can change the following things: sounds, music, flash block
    hits and show start animation. You can preset these options with
    the @{"configuration file" link CONFIGFILE}.

  @{IT "QUIT GAME"}
  @{IT "~~~~~~~~~"}
    Guess ??? Right !!! Here you quit back to AmigaDOS or Workbench.
    Do you really want to leave this great game ? Oh, you want to
    create some levels with @{"your registered copy of the editor" link EDITOR}.

@endnode
@node GAMESCREEN "Arkanos V3.0 - Game Screen"

    @{HI "The Playing Screen"}
   @{HI "~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~"}

  At the top you can see this information panel:

      +-----------++----------+----------------------------+
      | ######### || /=\ x### | DIAMONDS  EXTRA  BONUS x## |
      ++---------+++---+----+-+--+----+----+----+----+----++
      || Ox##### ||    |    |    |    |    |    |    |    ||

  It has totally changed since version 2.1, so please read this section
  at least once.
  First of all the bonus points have been removed. On the top left
  corner you can see you current score. To the right is the number of
  paddles. And the large box further right contains the bonus items.
  You can collect 8 diamonds, 5 letters that spells the word EXTRA and
  5 letters that spells the word BONUS. Right to the word BONUS you
  see the score multiplicator.
  On the bottom line you see your money on the left. And there are
  eight slots for some bonus items.

  Under it is the level area. On the bottom you have your paddle and
  the left edge contains the ball storage. There is a limited room
  for 40 balls. More balls are stored "outside" the screen and the
  storage is automatically refilled if you launch a new ball. With
  version 3.0 you must also keep track of your balls you are playing
  with! Click the right mouse button to launch a ball. You must remove
  all blocks from the level. For each block you remove you get points
  depending on the speed of the balls. You can launch more balls if
  you want, but don't let them fall down! There are 16 balls allowed
  to play. When you remove normal blocks there may be bonus items
  falling down. Catch them with the paddle to get extras.
  When all blocks have been removed you must shoot all balls back to
  the storage. There is an entry on the top left corner of the level.
  To make it easier the entry start to soak in near balls.

  While playing the balls starts moving faster. The ball speed at the
  start of the level is 6, quite comfortable. If the speed reaches 16
  it will be quite challenging to keep multiple balls on the level.
  The maximum speed is 36. If the speed would reach 37, the ball trap
  mechanism removes all indestructable and special blocks and the ball
  speed is set 6.
  If the balls are trapped in a wall labyrinth this mechanism won't
  help you much. You can try to shake the level with the <SPACE> bar.
  But not too much! All balls change the moving direction. Use this
  feature wisely to finish the levels faster. You hear a warning
  sound -- if sounds are enabled -- and the background flashes white
  when the next use would cause a TILT. In this case the paddle would
  freezes so that you will finally loose all balls. Wait at least 10
  seconds after the warning before you use the <SPACE> bar again.

  You loose your paddle if all balls fall down. Then the @{I}BONUSTIMER @{UI}
  is reduced by two seconds and a new paddle appears. Launch new balls
  to continue. The game is over if you have no paddles anymore @{B}OR@{UB}
  you have no balls in the storage! Have always on eye on the number
  of balls.
  You get a free ball at 20000 points. For the next ball you need 2000
  points more, that is 22000. The next free ball is at 42000 points,
  then with 66000 points and so on. The same applies to free paddles.
  You get the first free paddle with 100000 points. For the next one
  you need 20000 points more. The next free paddle is at 220000 points,
  then with 360000 points and so on.

  After you have cleared the level you can see the level statistic.
  For more details click on the "STATISTIC" button and you can see
  the statistic screen.
  If you have save-tokens you can click the "SAVE" button to save the
  current game. Every 5 levels you get a free save-token to save your
  game. But there are other ways to get save-tokens.
  With the button "ENTER SHOP" you enter the shop where you can buy
  save-tokens. If you save the game you cannot enter the shop anymore.

  There are 50 levels in each level set. If you solved all of them you
  start from the beginning, with less good bonus items and more bad
  bonus items. This happens four times, so level 200 is finally the
  last one. At the end you get 40000 points bonus for clearing all
  levels. When you mix the levels you get 100000 points! For each left
  paddle you get 5000 points. Your left money is multiplied by five
  and added to your score. And for each save-token you get 1000 points.

  That's it. Your final score will be tested for the top ten high
  score list. You may enter your name (at most 24 characters). After
  that the new high score with the statistic will be saved to disc.
  UNPROTECT YOUR FLOPPY OR THE HIGHSCORE WILL NOT BE SAVED!!

