    Click to read more about save-tokens ->->->->->->->-> @{" click me " link SAVETOKENS}

@endnode
@node CONFIGFILE "Arkanos V3.0 - The Configuration File"

    @{HI "How to configure Arkanos"}
   @{HI "~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~"}

  When the programm start, you can see the big LOADING... text. Under
  it you see what the programm loads. It's in dark grey, so you should
  not bother about it if everything is okay.

  All information is saved in the file "Arkanos3.Config". Lines starting
  with semicolons (;) are comments, they are ignored. The first four
  items set the directories for the game font, the levels, the graphics,
  the language files and the save games. You can use any legal AmigaDOS
  path here, even logical assigns if they exist at programm start. You
  need no slash (/) at the end of directories.

  Next you see the files to use. The game font and the language can't
  be changed. The level-set can be changed in the main menu. Next follow
  the game options. The first four can be changed and saved in the
  options menu. And the bottom three can be changed on the main menu.

  At the end is the module list. Enter your modules you want to use
  while playing the game with full path. You can load 100 modules if
  you have enough memory. But remember: the module must be moved
  to chip memory that it can be played. If you have just 512K of chip
  memory you may only load small modules (<50K). With 1MB of chip memory
  you can load large modules (>150K) too.
  Have a look at the options menu. There you see how many modules have
  been loaded into fast memory. You also see the size of the largest
  module and a status if it can be played:
    *) red:    There is not enough free chip memory. Not all modules
               can be played, only the small ones.
    *) yellow: There is enough free chip memory, but the required
               amount may not be in a continuous region. There may
               be playing problems with large modules.
    *) green:  Everything is okay, all modules should be playable.

  You have to edit the file to play you own modules. I have my modules
  in "Dh1:Musik/Module", so with my file probably no modules are loaded.

@endnode
