@node INSTALL "Install to HD, Floppy or WinUAE"


  Requirements:
  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~
   -> An Amiga, not too slow (mine is 68030 with 25 Mhz and FPU)
   -> Memory: 612K chip, 740K fast to run, 1156K disc space to install
   -> Workbench 2.0 (or above) to run that thing. The game does not
      run with WB 1.3 or lower. So please upgrade! (thanks, Mario!)
      With some accessories running in the background problems may
      occur. Please turn them off and start the game again. (I have
      MagicMenu V2.21 and Toolmanager V2.1 running without problems.)


  Install to hard disc:
  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
      Only copy all files into your desired drawer. Configure the
      game as you like with the @{"Arkanos3.Config" link CONFIGFILE} file.


  Install to floppy disc:
  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
      The game grows, so it doesn't fit on a single floppy anymore. Read
      the WinUAE section below how to setup multiple disks.


  Install on WinUAE:
  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
      Depending on how you want to play you can install to an emulated
      hard disk or use floppy disc images. Because I've programmed and
      tested most parts under WinUAE I don't expect problems. Create
      at least two empty discs.
      The first disk is the boot disk, so make it bootable and add the
      following files with their directories:

        c/endcli
        c/loadwb
        libs/mathtrans.library
        libs/icon.library

      Create the file @{I} s/startup-sequence @{UI} with this content:

        LoadWB
        EndCLI

      Now rename the first disk to "ARKANOS3" and copy all files that
      will never change:

        Arkanos
        Arkanos.info
        Arkanos3.Anim
        Arkanos3.Config
        Arkanos3.Data
        ArkanosD.Guide
        ArkanosD.Guide.info
        ArkanosE.Guide
        ArkanosE.Guide.info
        Loading.Data

      Finally change the "Arkanos3.Config" file. Add "ARKANOS3_DATA:"
      in front of the directories names. (But after the = symbol.)
      Now you can create and compressed ADZ image from the first
      disk. But remember that you can't change the configuration!

      Now rename the second disk to "ARKANOS3_DATA" and copy the
      remaining directories:

        Fonts/...
        Graphics/...
        Languages/...
        Levels/...
        Saves/...

      That's it. Don't compress the second disk. You would not be
      able to save your high scores. You may add your @{"editor" link EDITOR}
      on the second disk. If you have problems, you can have my
      configuration and ADF files.

@endnode
