@node STATSCREEN "Arkanos V3.0 - Statistic Screen"

    @{HI "The Statistic Screen"}
   @{HI "~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~"}

  On the left you see the graphics area, and on the right are some
  information and you can choose between these 5 graphic types:
  - SCORE: Here you see your score. There are four different types
        from bottom to top: GREEN for memory games, YELLOW for bonus
        levels, ORANGE for jackpots and RED for normal points.
  - LIVES: Here you see two lines. A RED line shows the number of
        paddles and a YELLOW line shows the number of balls.
  - MONEY: Here you see a line with the amount of money after you
        quit the final level information.
  - BONUS: Here you see a line how much bonus items you have
        collected.
  - BLIST: That's the final statistic from version 1.2. Here you see
        all bonus items with their relative percentage and the number
        in the box tells you how often you have collected the bonus.

  With the double arrow in the bottom right corner you can zoom in/out
  the graphic area. Click here at the BLIST to change between
  percentages and absolute values. Use the sliders and arrows to
  scroll the graphic.
  At zoom level 3 or higher you can place the mouse pointer on the
  colors and you see a small box with the level and the value. And,
  finally, click the "EXIT" button to exit the statistic.

@endnode
@node BLOCKTYPES "Arkanos V3.0 - Block Types"

  @{HI "SCORE UP"}
    This increases your score by 1 to 16 points. Very great block
    with BREAKTHROUGH bonus activated.

  @{HI "SCORE DOWN"}
    This decreases your score by 1 to 16 points. Always avoid this
    block, especially with the BREAKTHROUGH bonus.

  @{HI "SPEED UP"}
    Increases ball speed by one up to speed 34. Can you still follow
    the ball with your eyes ? If you bought the SPEED LIMIT item in
    the shop the speed increases up to speed 16.

  @{HI "SPEED DOWN"}
    Decreases ball speed by one down to speed 4. Very boring, don't
    you think ? I fall asleep... Zzzz

  @{HI "RANDOM DIRECTION"}
    The ball leaves this block at random direction.

  @{HI "MOVING BLOCK"}
    Hit this block and it will move one position depending how the
    ball hits the block. The new position must be free. TRY IT !!!

  @{HI "INDESTRUCT"}
    This block can't be destroyed. After many hits the ball changed
    the moving direction a little bit (DX or DY ±1). That's only to
    prevent the ball from infinite loops and makes the game more
    interesting.

  @{HI "1-HIT INDESTRUCT"}
    Hit this block once and it changes to an INDESTRUCT block.

  @{HI "SHORT CUT"}
    The ball will disappear, and appear at the other end of the short
    cut. It's also possible that the ball will change its direction a
    little bit to avoid loopings between short-cuts.

  @{HI "DYNAMITE"}
    Hit this flashing block will explode all 8 surrounding blocks, if
    there are some. If there is another DYNAMITE block around, a chain
    reaction starts. But these blocks always counts 8 points, no matter
    what the ball speed is.

  @{HI "DYNAMITE LIGHT"}
    Like the dynamite block above, but here only other dynamite blocks
    explode. It's like a fuse.

  @{HI "DYNAMITE BLOCK"}
    Also like the dynamite block, but here instead of free space normal
    blocks are left you have to remove.

  @{HI "5-HIT BLOCK"}
    Hit this block and it will be reduced to a 4-HIT BLOCK.

  @{HI "4-HIT BLOCK"}
    Hit this block and it will be reduced to a 3-HIT BLOCK.

  @{HI "3-HIT BLOCK"}
    Hit this block and it will be reduced to a 2-HIT BLOCK.

  @{HI "2-HIT BLOCK"}
    Hit this block and it will become a normal block, the grey one.

  @{HI "4-HIT EXPANDER"}
    This will expand at the edges to 3-HIT EXPANDER. There must be
    a free field or normal size blocks. The larger blocks, walls and
    the jackpot fields are not replaced!

  @{HI "3-HIT EXPANDER"}
    This will expand at the edges to 2-HIT EXPANDER, if possible.

  @{HI "2-HIT EXPANDER"}
    This will expand at the edges to 1-HIT EXPANDER, if possible.

  @{HI "1-HIT EXPANDER"}
    This will expand at the edges to a normal block, the white one,
    if possible.

  @{HI "NORMAL BLOCKS"}
    Just hit these blocks once and they disappear. The colours are
    just to make the level friendlier. But you just have white blocks
    in your own level set if you want.

  @{HI "BIG BLOCKS"}
    This blocks splits into 2 normal blocks of the same colour.

  @{HI "LARGE BLOCKS"}
    This blocks splits into 2 big blocks of the same colour.

  @{HI "WALL BLOCKS"}
    Can't be destroyed, can't be removed and finally you also can't
    move though it. Just walls !!! Be careful at diagonal walls.

  @{HI "WALL BLOCKS WITH PIPES"}
    Can't be destroyed and removed either, but if your ball hits the
    pipes entrance it will go through. The ball speed and entry angle
    will stay the same at the exit !!! On the T-crossings the ball
    randomly chooses a direction.

  @{HI "JACKPOT FIELDS"}
    On some levels there are 8 to 16 jackpot fields. Lock balls in all
    fields and you win the jackpot score. Not every ball will lock if
    you hit a field. Instead the jackpot score grows and the ball will
    be released after a short time. When you win the jackpot score all
    balls are released and the ball storage entry soaks in balls for
    30 seconds.

@endnode
@node BONUSITEMS "Arkanos V3.0 - Bonus Items"

  Every bonus item counts 10 points. Every 50 levels, so after you
  have played a complete level-set, you get less good items, but more
  bad items. The symbol '-' after the bonus items here are bad items.
  The symbol '+' after the items here are good ones.
  And from level 101 to 200 the bonus tiles will be hidden in the
  upper part of the level area. So you've just a second to look at
  it and decide to take or not. THINK QUICK!

  @{HI "GET KILLED"}  -
    You loose the current paddle. But get 40 points, instead of 10!
    The balls stay on the level and continue moving when the new
    paddle appears.

  @{HI "SCORE DOWN"}  -
    This bonus decreases your points by about 200 to 400.

  @{HI "SCORE UP"}  +
    This bonus increases your points by about 100 to 400.

  @{HI "SLOW BALL"}   +
    Decreases ball speed by 4. You need more SLOW BALL if the speed is
    about 20 or higher for a better playing speed. Minimum speed is 4.

  @{HI "RESTART LEVEL"}  -
    Re-initialize the current level. If there are only a few special
    blocks is a good choice to take it. Otherwise your balls may be
    trapped, or it is hard to hit some blocks. Bonus levels can't be
    restarted, but you get 200 points, instead of just 10.

  @{HI "SHRINK PADDLE"}  -
    This bonus decreases your paddle size by one. You loose 16 pixels
    to catch the ball. Minimum size is 1. It's very hard to get the
    ball with that short paddle.

  @{HI "EXPAND PADDLE"}  +
    This bonus increases your paddle size by one. This means 16 pixels
    extra space to get the ball. Maximum size is 8, so your paddle is
    at the most 128 pixels large. This is about half of the total
    level width. This could become a big problem.

  @{HI "CATCH BALL"}  +
    This bonus activates the catch field on your paddle. This is the flashing
    line at the top of your paddle. Click the left mouse button to
    release all balls. If you take this bonus twice, the catch field
    will be deactivated.

  @{HI "BREAKTHROUGH"}  +
    If you take this bonus the balls will move through all blocks,
    except the SHORT CUT and WALLS. But I must warn you: If there are
    many BALL SPEED UP blocks, the balls will .. .  .   .    .  AWAY!
    But it's very useful with many SCORE UP blocks. Take this bonus
    again, and the balls behave normal.

  @{HI "SPLIT BALL"}  +
    This item splits free moving balls. If you play with one ball it
    will split into three balls. If you play with more balls each
    ball will split in two balls. In the best case you need four items
    to reach the ball limit. (1->3->6->12->16)
    Balls are not free, if they are in a SHORT-CUT, in a WALL PIPE,
    trapped in a JACKPOT FIELD or catched on the paddle! If you see
    a ball that doesn't split the ball limit has been reached.

  @{HI "LASER PADDLE"}  +
    This bonus activates the lasers on your paddle. The paddle will
    change. Use left mouse button to fire laser. Don't fire them too
    often. Every mouse click resets your laser, even if you didn't
    hit anything. Remember this if you want to fire at blocks on the
    top of the level.
    You can never shoot walls, but very effective with BREAKTHROUGH
    bonus. But blocks hit with the laser don't drop bonus items and
    count 8 points only! If you already have a laser paddle, the
    laser will be deactivated.

  @{HI "SCORE JACKPOT"}  +
    If there are JACKPOT FIELDS you get 1 percent of the current
    jackpot score, otherwise only the 10 points for the item.

  @{HI "ZAP EXPANDER"}  -
    This removes all expanding blocks on the level. Warning: Expanding
    blocks can be used to break through INDESTRUCT blocks, and if you
    remove them... 8-)

  @{HI "ZAP SPECIAL"}  +
    This removes all special blocks: SCORE UP, SCORE DOWN, BALL SPEED
    UP, BALL SPEED DOWN, RANDOM DIRECTION and MOVING BLOCK. If there
    are only SCORE UP blocks, don't take it. Otherwise think quickly
    if you want to remove those blocks.

  @{HI "ZAP INDESTRUCT"}  +
    This removes all indestructible attributes of the level. This
    means: INDESTRUCT will be removed completely, 1-HIT INDESTRUCT
    will be replaced by a normal block (the red one) and 5, 4, 3,
    2-HIT BLOCKS will also be replaced by a normal block (the grey
    one). BIG and LARGE blocks change to normal block of their colour.

  @{HI "MORE DYNAMITE"}  +
    Expand all exploding blocks, one the each side: up, down, left
    and right. But remember: exploding blocks only count 8 points.
    Nevertheless it's a very effective way to complete a level. BIG
    and LARGE blocks will not change. WALLS are also not affected.

  The following 10 items are timed. You see the corresponding timers
  on the information screen. Each time you take one of these items the
  value of the @{I}BONUSTIMER @{UI}is added. The @{I}BONUSTIMER @{UI}starts at 10 seconds,
  this is the minimum value. You can -- and you really should --
  increase the timer.

  @{HI "GRAVITY"}  -
    This actives the gravity field at the bottom of the screen. The
    field starts approximately in the middle of the level. It reduces
    the ball speed by 2, but minimum speed is 4. The timer uses slot 1,
    the left most one right next to you money. You cannot have GRAVITY
    and MAGNETISM at the same time.

  @{HI "MAGNETISM"}  -
    Actives the magnetic field at the bottom of the screen so that
    the ball is deflected to the side edges. It starts approximately
    in the middle of the level. It reduces the ball speed by 2, but
    minimum speed is 4. The timer uses slot 1, the left most one
    right next to you money. You cannot have GRAVITY and MAGNETISM
    at the same time.

  @{HI "FOLLOW BALLS"}  -
    Your paddle will automatically follow the lowest ball in the lower
    part of the level area. If all balls are in the upper area you can
    move the paddle. Don't trust on this bonus too much if you play
    with multiple balls. The automatic system is somehow slow and may
    loose a ball, especially if there are balls nearly at the same
    horizontal line. Warning: You may be forced to take bonus items
    you don't want to have and you may loose bonus items you would
    like to collect. This bonus uses timer slot 2.

  @{HI "GUARD"}  +
    Activate a bottom wall to close the level. No balls can fall down
    now. And bonus items are also trapped! They stay on the wall for
    five seconds, and then they explode. A quite good bonus, except
    you have an ATTRACT type bonus. Shit!!! This bonus uses timer
    slot 3.

  @{HI "NIGHT"}  -
    This darkens the level down. It's harder to play, so you get 2
    extra points for all block hits. You see the timer in slot
    number 4.

  @{HI "EXPLODE BALL"}  +
    A good helper, especially with lot's of indestruct blocks. Your
    balls became deadly explosives. All blocks you hit now explode
    like dynamite blocks. Luckily you have a very robust paddle! But
    remember that exploding blocks only count 8 points. This bonus
    use timer slot number 5.

  @{HI "ATTRACT BAD"}  -
    This is a quite annoying bonus. All bad items will move to you
    paddle. Dangerous with the GUARD bonus !!! This bonus uses timer
    slot number 6.

  @{HI "ATTRACT GOOD"}  +
    This helps you to collect good bonus items. All diamonds and
    letters are good items too. This could be annoying if you're just
    missing one diamond or letter, but get the wrong one! You see
    this timer in slot 7.

  @{HI "SCORE×2"}  +
    All your points are doubled! This includes collecting bonus items,
    diamonds and bonus letters. You see this timer in slot number 8,
    the right most one. You cannot have SCORE×2 and SCORE×5 at the
    same time!

  @{HI "SCORE×5"}  +
    It's like the SCORE×2 above, but points counts five times. It
    uses timer slot number 8 too. You cannot have SCORE×2 and SCORE×5
    at the same time!

  Now the remaining normal bonus items follow. They are more valueable
  and appear less often than the previous ones.

  @{HI "REDUCE BONUSTIMER"}  -
    Reduces the @{I}BONUSTIMER @{UI}by one second. Minimum is 10 seconds. Avoid
    this item if possible!

  @{HI "INCREASE BONUSTIMER"}  +
    This increases the @{I}BONUSTIMER @{UI}by two seconds. Always take it!

  @{HI "BONUS LEVEL MULTIPLIER"}  +
    Increase the bonus level multiplier by one. Wait some time to
    collect all BONUS letter and collect more of these items. You can
    score much more points.

  @{HI "FINISH LEVEL"}  +
    This brings you to the next level straight away. No need to shoot
    the balls back to the storage. Remember all the left points on
    the level before you take it. The next level may be harder. Think
    quickly, if it's worth. ;-)

  @{HI "EXTRA BALL"}  +
    You get a new ball on the paddle, where you catch this item, but
    only if there less than 16 balls on the level. Click the left
    mouse button to release the new ball.

  @{HI "EXTRA PADDLE"}  +
    Gives you an extra paddle, but removes all extras, like CATCH,
    LASER PADDLE and BREAKTHROUGH. Maybe these bonus items make it
    easier to solve the level. Think quickly, if you really need an
    extra paddle.

  Now the special items follow. Don't take all of them. If you already
  have one of these items you will loose it! And at the bottom some
  information about the coins.

  @{HI "BONUS DIAMONDS"}  +
    There are 8 different coloured bonus diamonds. If you catch all
    8 diamonds you get three extra balls and one paddle. One diamond
    counts 200 points. It's hard to let them fall down, but you will
    really need many balls and paddles on higher levels!  8-)

  @{HI "EXTRA LETTERS"}  +
    Collect the 5 letters E.X.T.R.A. and you can play a @{"memory game" link MEMORYGAME}.
    Each letter counts 100 points. See there for more information.

  @{HI "BONUS LETTERS"}  +
    Collect the 5 letters B.O.N.U.S. and you can play a @{"bonus level" link BONUSLEVEL}.
    As basic value you get 100 points. For each bonus multiplier you
    get 50 points more. So with multiplier 2 you get 150 points and,
    for example, with multiplier 6 you get 350 points.
    Hard to decide here: With multiplier 8 and SCORE×5 bonus you get
    incredible 2250 points! And if you already have this letter and
    only one is left, difficult...

  @{HI "COINS"}  +
    Sometimes also coins appear. The values are 10, 20, 50, 100, 200
    and 500. The lower values are more possible than the large values.
    With this money you can buy improvements in the @{"shop" link SHOP} after each
    level.

@endnode
@node MEMORYGAME "Arkanos 3.0 - The Memory Game"

    @{HI "The Memory Sub-Game"}
   @{HI "~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~"}

  You enter a memory game if you collect all 5 letters of the word
  EXTRA. If the shop is closed you can also enter a memory game
  instead. Then you need 600 to 1200 money, or the corresponding
  number of save-tokens, between 1 and 3. You know the objective of
  this game ???
  There are 60 fields with pairs of different types. Click with left
  mouse button to open two fields. If the symbols are the same you
  win something and you get 100 points. You play against the time.
  You get double the @{I}BONUSTIMER @{UI}plus one minute. You see the time
  in the lower right corner under the playing field. Left to the time
  you see the number of remaining pairs. In the lower left corner you
  see your score and money. On the bottom you see all pairs you have
  found in order.
  If you run out of time all remaining fields are opened. Have a look
  on which pairs you missed. When you find all pairs the remaining
  fields are opened and you get 50 points for each left second and
  200 money as bonus.

  These symbols are available:

  @{IT "Coins"}
    It's identical to the bonus items. About 25 percent of the fields
    are coins. The lower values appear more often.

  @{IT "KILL"}
    If you open this symbol as first symbol the memory game is over.
    If you open this symbol as second symbol you loose 10 seconds.

  @{IT "SCORE DOWN"}
    Reduce the points of the memory game by 100 to 300. Note: you
    must also take these pairs to win the final bonus!

  @{IT "SCORE UP"}
    Increase the points of the memory game by 200 to 500.

  @{IT "EXPAND PADDLE"}
    Increase the size of the paddle. If you alread have the largest
    paddle you get 800 points.

  @{IT "CATCH PADDLE"}
    Activate the catch paddle. If you already have it you get 400
    points.

  @{IT "BRICKTHROUGH"}
    Activate the breakthrough balls. If you already have this ball
    you get 600 points.

  @{IT "LASER PADDLE"}
    Activate the laser on your paddle. If you already have the
    laser you get 400 points.

  @{IT "ZAP EXTRA"}
    Randomly explode a single memory tile. If there are only pairs
    left on the playing field nothing happens.

  @{IT "DYNAMITE"}
    Randomly explode two KILL fields. If no field explode, or just
    one field explode, then no other KILL fields exists.

  @{IT "SCORE×2"}
    Doubles the money! Not the points! Remember them to the end of
    the game, but watch the time.

  @{IT "SCORE×5"}
    Your points of the memory game are multiplied by five! Remember
    them to the end of the game, but watch the time.

  @{IT "EXTRA TIME"}
    Increases the @{I}BONUSTIMER @{UI}by one second and the current
    memory game time by 10 seconds.

  @{IT "BONUS MULTIPLIER"}
    Increase the bonus level multiplier by one.

  @{IT "NEXT LEVEL"}
    Display a level preview of the next level only once. After that,
    or if you played the last level, you get 1200 points. If you play
    a bonus level no preview is displayed, but you get 400 points.

  @{IT "EXTRA BALL"}
    An extra ball will be added to the ball storage.

  @{IT "EXTRA PADDLE"}
    One extra paddle. As pair very rare!

@endnode
@node BONUSLEVEL "Arkanos V3.0 - All about bonus levels"

  If you collect all 5 letters of the word BONUS, the letters starts to
  flash and you enter one of the ten possible bonus levels. This depends
  on the level-set. It may have only one bonus level. All timed bonus
  items are cleared and the following upgrades are stored: paddle size,
  catch, laser and brickthrough.

  Then you play the bonus level like any other level. If you get the
  KILL bonus or all balls fall down the bonus level ends. You can win
  the jackpot in the bonus level only once. After you win the jackpot
  all catcher fields are removed. At the end you see this report:

        Bonus level points
      - Money bonus (5% normal exit or 10% when level is cleared)
      = subtotal
      × bonus level multiplier
      = final bonus level score

  Clear? Okay. If you cleared the bonus level you also get an extra
  @{"save-token" link SAVETOKENS}. Click mouse button to continue with
  the normal level.
  It is possible to play a memory game from the bonus level. But it
  is NOT possible to play another bonus level. If you collect all 5
  letters of the word BONUS within a bonus level you get 2000 points
  instead. And you cannot restart a bonus level.

@endnode
@node SHOP "Arkanos V3.0 - The Shop"

  At the end of each level you can enter the shop. The prices change
  after each level. You can buy the following items. The values near
  the items are the base prices at the beginning of the game.

  @{IT "INCREASE PADDLE"}    (320)
    Increase the paddle size by one (16 pixels). You can buy it at
    most 5 times. Then you have the largest paddle. Holds until you
    loose the paddle.

  @{IT "CATCH PADDLE"}    (520)
    Activate the catch zone on your paddle, the flashing line. Click
    left mouse button to release the ball. Holds until you loose the
    paddle.

  @{IT "LASER PADDLE"}    (800)
    Activate the laser paddle. Click left mouse button to fire the
    bullets. Holds until you loose the paddle.

  @{IT "BREAKTHROUGH"}    (1020)
    Here the balls will move through all blocks, except the SHORT CUT
    and WALLS. See the BREAKTHROUGH bonus item for details. Holds
    until you loose the paddle.

  @{IT "EXPLODE BALL"}    (760)
    Activate the exploding balls. See the EXPLODE BALL bonus item for
    details. Holds for double of the @{I}BONUSTIMER @{UI} plus 30 seconds.

  @{IT "GUARD"}    (920)
    Activate the bottom wall that closes the level. See the GUARD
    bonus item for details. Holds for double of the @{I}BONUSTIMER @{UI}
    plus 30 seconds.

  @{IT "EXTRA SECOND"}    (260)
    Adds one second to your @{I}BONUSTIMER.@{UI}

  @{IT "SAVE-TOKEN"}    (600)
    A @{"save-token" link SAVETOKENS} to save your game, or to enter future @{"memory games" link MEMORYGAME}.

  @{IT "LEVEL PREVIEW"}    (180)
    Display a small preview of the next level. Use it to decide if you
    need to buy certain other items.

  @{IT "MORE BONUS ITEMS"}    (880)
    Increase the probability to appear bonus items. Do you really need
    more bonus items?

  @{IT "EXPAND DIAGONAL WALLS"}    (680)
    Replace all diagonal walls with the next bigger rectangular
    version. Be careful at small passages: you may close them!
    Examples:      __            ___          _____
          /|      |  |          |   \\        |     |
         / |  to  |  |    or    |    \\   to  |     |
        /__|      |__|          |_____\\      |_____|

  @{IT "REDUCE DIAGONAL WALLS"}    (1080)
    Replace all diagonal walls with the next smaller rectangular
    version.
    Examples: ___          __
             |   \\        |  |            /\\
             |    \\   to  |  |    or     /  \\   will be removed
             |_____\\      |__|          /____\\

  @{IT "SPEEDLIMIT"}    (840)
    Normally the maximum ball speed is 36. This halves the maximum
    ball speed to 18. Hold for the following level.

  @{IT "DOUBLE SCORE"}    (1200)
    This doubles all scores on the next level. Use it for full levels
    with lots of blocks.

  @{IT "EXTRA BALL"}    (220)
    Add an extra ball. Always have an eye on the ball storage. On
    some levels you need to lock 16 balls to win the jackpot score.

  @{IT "EXTRA PADDLE"}    (1440)
    Hmmm, guess? Right! An extra paddle if you have so much money.
    But think about the bonus points at the end of the game!

  If you have not enough money you can sell paddles for half of the
  buying price. The price will fall a little bit.

  Sometimes the shop may be closed! Instead you can enter a memory
  game to win upgrades, points and money.

@endnode
@node SAVETOKENS "Arkanos V3.0 - All about save tokens"

  In version 2.0 I noticed that saving after each level can be used to
  maximize you score and paddles. After you have finished a level you
  save the game. If playing the next level is not as good as you would
  like it to be, you press the <ESC> key and reload the game until you
  get the desired bonus items. Then you save the game and repeat this
  procedure.
@{JCENTER}
@{B}THAT WAS NOT THE INTENDED PHILOSOPHY !!!!@{UB}
@{JLEFT}
  That's why I've added the save-tokens in version 2.1. Now you need
  one save-token to save the current game. You get a save-token
    (1) every 5 levels,
    (2) buy it in the shop, or
    (3) if you have cleared a bonus level.

  The "SAVE-RELOAD"-method is now more difficult to play and should
  not be used anymore. And don't try to hack the save file.
  You will FAIL!!! (I know that this is an unwanted invitation to
  do it, but I don't care. It's you spare time you're wasting!)

@endnode
