@node KNOWN_BUGS "What's wrong with the game ?"

  No strange things happend while play-testing the game, but if you
  find something, please let me know. If it is possible (game not
  crashed) use the F4 key to generate a debug output and send me the
  files from the "Debug" folder. A save game is also very useful.
  Please answer the following questions with your report:

   - Does the game quit with an error message? If so, please write it
     down and try to explain WHEN this happens. WHAT did you do before?

   - Does the game behave strange? Maybe incorrect, not like above !!!

   - Is it a memory problem? (Then I need your configuration.)

   - Did the program completely refuse to load? (Missing files.)

   - Is the game too slow, no smooth moving? (Configuation, please.)

   - Did Mr. GURU visit you? (Oh, dear. Did you read the @{"legal stuff" link LEGAL}?)
     Write down the first 8 hex digits and contact @{"me" link INFOS}.

  Hitting block corners:  NO BUG !!!

    It's not difficult to explain what really happens. Every physics
    teacher can tell you about that. But the details are very complex,
    because physical factors determine how the ball will continue his
    way. For this game it would be too difficult to add all factors.
    So I decided to reflect balls like diagonal walls or to ignore it.

  Ball is trapped in a wall block:  GREAT BUG !!!

